<header class="entry-header clr">
	<h1 class="single-post-title entry-title" itemprop="headline">Have an Idea to Improve the Indian Railways? You Could Win a Rs 10 Lakh Prize!</h1><!-- .single-post-title -->
</header><!-- .entry-header -->

<p class="subtitle">If your idea to help the Railways is viable, you could get lucky!</p>

<ul class="meta clr">

	
					<li class="meta-author" itemprop="name"><span class="screen-reader-text">Post Author:</span><i class="icon-user" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="https://www.thebetterindia.com/author/rayomand-engineer/" title="Posts by Rayomand Engineer" rel="author"  itemprop="author" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="https://schema.org/Person">Rayomand Engineer</a></li>
		
		
		
		
		
	
		
					<li class="meta-date" itemprop="datePublished"><span class="screen-reader-text">Post published:</span><i class="icon-clock" aria-hidden="true"></i>March 27, 2018</li>
		
		
		
		
	
		
		
		
					<li class="meta-cat"><span class="screen-reader-text">Post Category:</span><i class="icon-folder" aria-hidden="true"></i><a href="https://www.thebetterindia.com/topics/news/" rel="category tag">News</a> <span class="owp-sep">/</span> <a href="https://www.thebetterindia.com/topics/news/quick-bytes/" rel="category tag">Quick Bytes</a> <span class="owp-sep">/</span> <a href="https://www.thebetterindia.com/topics/railway/" rel="category tag">Railway</a></li>
		
		
	
</ul>



<div class="entry-content clr" itemprop="text">
	<div class="adp-wrapper adp-post-ad-item" data-id="6"><div class="adp-container container"><div class="adp-banner"><div class="adp-heading">Promotion</div><!-- /.adp-heading --><div class="adp-banner-item"><a href="https://shop.thebetterindia.com/home-cleaner-kits-tbi/4-pack-kit?utm_source=thebetterindia.com&#038;utm_medium=bannerad-hp&#038;utm_campaign=hp-DiaMirza-21Nov" class="adp-banner-link" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" src="https://thebetterindia-english.sgp1.digitaloceanspaces.com/uploads/2020/11/AP_Dia_231120.jpg" alt="Ad Banner" class="adp-banner-img" width="500" height="500" ></a> <!-- /.adp-banner-link --></div><!-- /.adp-banner-item --></div><!-- /.adp-banner --></div><!-- /.adp-container --></div><!-- /.adp-wrapper --><p><span style="font-size: 42px; color: #9d1717;">T</span>he Indian Railways has always been serious about feedback. For example, based on the feedback they received over a period of time, they installed POS machines on trains, so that passengers could get a bill and stop complaining about overcharging. Read more about it <a href="https://www.thebetterindia.com/135413/irctc-to-install-pos-machines-on-trains-for-compulsory-billing-of-food/">here</a>.</p>
<p>This is not the only instance. Be it the introduction of separate ladies compartments, or other vital amenities; the national transporter has continually tried to improve its services.</p><div class="adp-wrapper adp-post-ad-item" data-id="5"><div class="adp-container container"><div class="adp-banner"><iframe src="https://anchor.fm/evolution-of-solutions/embed/episodes/Episode-4-Virtual-Reality-Ft--Sairam-Sagiraju--Filmmaker--Tithi-Tiwar--Trezi-ejlnee" height="102px" width="400px" frameborder="0" scrolling="no"></iframe></div><!-- /.adp-banner --></div><!-- /.adp-container --></div><!-- /.adp-wrapper -->
<h2>Well, the Railways is once again inviting you to present a viable solution to any issues you might have faced while taking a train. Stop being an armchair activist, cease the grumbling, and work on a solution.</h2>
<figure id="attachment_131353" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-131353" style="width: 1200px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img class="size-full wp-image-131353" src="https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts.jpg" alt="Give the Railways a good solution, and walk away with a grand prize! Representative image only. Image Courtesy: Wikimedia Commons." width="1200" height="628" srcset="https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts.jpg 1200w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-300x157.jpg 300w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-768x402.jpg 768w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-500x262.jpg 500w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-364x190.jpg 364w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-758x397.jpg 758w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-608x318.jpg 608w, https://thebetterindia-english.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2018/02/Railways-recruitment-89000-posts-1152x603.jpg 1152w" sizes="(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-131353" class="wp-caption-text">Give the Railways a good solution, and walk away with a grand prize! Representative image only. Image Courtesy: Wikimedia Commons.</figcaption></figure>
<p>The best part is, if you win, you get paid for it. Rs 10 lakhs, to be exact.</p>
<p>Titled &#8216;How to Raise Money for Railways to Provide Better Services,&#8217; the competition guidelines invite contestants to send practical ways to raise money to help the Railways improve services, and good ideas stand to get huge cash prizes:</p>
<p>1) Rs 10 lakh for the winner<br />
2) Rs 5 lakh for the runner-up<br />
3) Rs 3 lakh for the second runner-up<br />
4) Rs 1 lakh for 4th place.</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s the background for the idea. The Railways Ministry <a href="https://www.ndtv.com/business/indian-railways-revamp-government-to-offer-rs-10-lakh-prize-for-idea-to-improve-irctc-1828388?amp=1&amp;akamai-rum=off&amp;__twitter_impression=true">says</a> the gross revenue of the Railways was Rs 1,65,292 crores while working expenses totalled Rs 1.59 lakh crore. The Railways revenue has been stagnant for the past four years, but working expenses have been rising, thus affecting service quality.</p>
<p><strong>So, this is how you can win Rs 10 lakh, courtesy the Railways.</strong></p>
<p>1) Visit <a href="https://innovate.mygov.in/">here</a> and click the &#8220;click to participate&#8221; button. You will be taken to a landing page featuring the registration form with various fields.</p>
<p>2) Fill the registration form and entry submission form, taking care to make sure the latter adheres to the guidelines mentioned in the same.</p><div class="adp-wrapper adp-post-ad-item" data-id="3"><div class="adp-container container"><div class="adp-banner"><div class="adp-heading">Promotion</div><!-- /.adp-heading --><div class="adp-banner-item"><a href="https://shop.thebetterindia.com/home-cleaner-kits-tbi/4-pack-kit?utm_source=thebetterindia.com&#038;utm_medium=bannerad-ap&#038;utm_campaign=ap1-DiaMirza-21Nov" class="adp-banner-link" target="_blank"><img loading="lazy" src="https://thebetterindia-english.sgp1.digitaloceanspaces.com/uploads/2020/11/Rev_Dia-Banner-800x800-1-1.png" alt="Ad Banner" class="adp-banner-img" width="500" height="500" ></a> <!-- /.adp-banner-link --></div><!-- /.adp-banner-item --></div><!-- /.adp-banner --></div><!-- /.adp-container --></div><!-- /.adp-wrapper -->
<p>3) Submit the required forms, and await your confirmation mail. If you have questions, send them to ps07@nair.rail.net.gov.in.</p>
<p>4) You will need to provide an idea for improving the Indian Railways revenue, in a maximum of 1000 words, with a 250 word abstract for the same. Make sure any attachments don&#8217;t exceed 8 MB. You will also need to submit a value proposition to customers and relevance of the concept in improving customer experience, in around 150 words. Next is a 250-word write-up in compliance with the boundary conditions. The originality of the idea must be written in 150 words. The cost-effectiveness of the project will span 200 words, with constraints taking up another 150 words.</p>
<p><strong>Criteria:-</strong><br />
This competition is open to individuals and companies/institutions.</p>
<p><strong>Deadline:-</strong><br />
Submit all the required information by 6:00 p.m., on 19th May.</p>
<p><strong>Language:-</strong><br />
Hindi/English can be used.</p>
<p><strong>Here are the various parameters, and how they affect total score:-</strong> The viability of project:- 30%<br />
Revenue potential:- 20%<br />
Customer Convenience:- 10%<br />
Scalability:- 10%<br />
Cost-Effectiveness:- 10%<br />
Compliance with boundary conditions:- 10%<br />
Detail orientation:- 5%<br />
Quality of presentation:- 5%</p>
<hr />
<p><strong><span style="color: #ff0000;">You may also like:- </span><span style="color: #ff6600;"><a style="color: #ff6600;" href="https://www.thebetterindia.com/97993/indian-railways-digitisation/">Indian Railways Is Now Set for a Complete Digital Revamp. Here’s What It Means.</a></span></strong></p>
<hr />
<p>So, if you have something you&#8217;d like to suggest, and you think it might work, do send your idea to the Railways and walk home with the Rs 10 lakh grand prize!</p>
